Load CDISCTealData object from a file

cdisc_data_file.Rd

cdisc_data_file(path, code = get_code(path))

Arguments

path

A (connection) or a (character)
string giving the pathname of the file or URL to read from. "" indicates the connection stdin.

code

(character)
reproducible code to re-create object

Value

CDISCTealData object

Examples

file_example <- tempfile(fileext = ".R")
writeLines(
  text = c(
    "library(scda)

     # code>
     ADSL <- synthetic_cdisc_data('latest')$adsl
     ADTTE <- synthetic_cdisc_data('latest')$adtte

     cdisc_data(
          cdisc_dataset(\"ADSL\", ADSL), cdisc_dataset(\"ADTTE\", ADTTE),
          code = \"ADSL <- synthetic_cdisc_data('latest')$adsl
                  ADTTE <- synthetic_cdisc_data('latest')$adtte\",
          check = FALSE
     )
     # <code"
  ),
  con = file_example
)

cdisc_data_file(file_example)
